title: Strong-willed
body:
Prompt - Hello love, I was wondering if you could do a one-shot about Joe Sugg being in a car accident with the rest of the buttercream gang and he is the worst off. I love your one-shots by the way!!!! Also you don’t have to worry about mine if you can do it because my birthday isn’t until June I’m in no rush and if you can’t don’t worry love that’s alright. :)

Prompt - Can you do one where Joe gets in a car accident and the others are really scared for him because they heard it was really bad but in the end he just has a concussion, broken leg, and a sprained wrist?


——

If you asked Zoe to describe her brother, she’d say that the boy was very strong-willed. And that could work both ways; good and bad. Joe, being strong-willed, was good in many ways as if it was usually the driving force behind all his big projects. It was that very determination that helped the boy to success. But sometimes, Joe’s stubbornness could really hurt the boy. If he sets his mind onto something, then it was difficult to convince him of otherwise. And that was a trait that Zoe didn’t like too much.

——

From childhood itself, Zoe had always warned Joe that she didn’t really see his stubbornness in a good eye. Like right now, in the late night, where Joe offered to go get the drinks to celebrate Zoe’s new book. Recently, Zoe had been really nervous of the reviews to her book but when it came out positive, her group of friends were there to congratulate her and that’s when Joe suggested that they celebrate the occasion.

“You don’t have to go so late in the night” Zoe tried to reason with her brother.

“What are you talking about? We absolutely have to celebrate this. It’s just a quick drive. I’ll be back soon” Joe insisted.

“I’ll come along” Jack Maynard said.

Zoe shared a look with Conor as the two of them watched their siblings go out in the night.

——

It was as if Zoe already had an intuition that something was wrong. Her heart had jumped up when she heard the phone call and watching Alfie’s expressions change to worry, had her already getting anxious.

“Joe and Jack got in a car accident.” Alfie explained as he grabbed his car keys.

Conor was already rushing out of the house when he heard about Jack being in a car accident but Zoe was frozen in her place.

“Let’s go, Zoe. He needs you” Louise said, wrapping an arm around Zoe’s shoulder.

Zoe felt like her body was on autopilot as she simply followed behind Louise.

——

When they got to the hospital, it had been a complete panic. Jack and Joe were being checked over and there was literally no information on how they were doing. They all sat waiting for any news concerning the boys when a doctor came out to inform them about Jack.

They followed the man to Jack’s room and Conor could finally breathe in a sigh of relief to see his little brother not too hurt.

“Oh kiddo, I got so worried” Conor sighed as he carefully brought the boy in a hug.

“Jack, you fine buddy?” Jim asked.

“I’m okay but Joe… Oh God, Joe… He was unconscious and bleeding” Jack said as he tried to get down the bed to see his friend.

“Hey… Hey… Calm down! You aren’t going anywhere buddy. We still don’t have any news regarding Joe but we’ll look after it alright” Alfie assured the boy.

Alfie turned around, sighing as he shared a look with Zoe, all while hoping that Joe was alright.

——

After quite some time, they were finally led to Joe’s room. Well, it did involve Alfie and Caspar literally threatening every medical staff that came their way for any kind of information concerning Joe.

“He got a concussion which probably is due to him hitting the steering wheel. He also has a broken leg and a sprained wrist. But he should be alright.” The doctor said.

“Oh God” Zoe broke down as she sat next to her little brother, holding onto his arm.

Alfie squeezed her shoulder, relieved to find that Joe was doing alright despite his injuries.

Now all they had to was to wait for Joe to wake up.

——

Joe woke up a few times but he finally regained full control over his senses on the next day when he woke up to murmurs around him.

“He probably passed out when his head hit the steering wheel and it must have scared Jack” Conor explained.

“Yeah, Jack had me proper worried when he panicked for Joe” Caspar chuckled.

Joe’s eyes snapped open when he heard Jack’s name and panicked as he looked out for his friend.

“Jack… Jack…” Joe mumbled.

“Jack is alright. He’s right there” Zoe said as she pointed to Jack sleeping in the other bed.

“Calm down man. It’s all okay now” Caspar said, patting Joe’s shoulder.

“All okay” Joe repeated, slightly dozing off.

“All okay except the fact that you’re so stubborn. Look where you stubbornness led you.” Zoe shook her head.

“I’m sleeping” Joe whispered.

“Sure and when you wake we’ll talk about how you should listen to me next time” Zoe chuckled.

“I’m asleep” Joe told her.

They all had a good chuckle at that.

——

Being strong-willed did help Joe a lot. He used as a motivation to get his projects and collabs done. He used it at home to get his way around with his parents. It came to help when he was down in situations like these where his will power helps him power his way to recovery and help motivate his friend, Jack, recover as well. But it also costs him quite a few things. As Zoe says, that stubbornness would end him in big trouble sometime but like any other big sister, she kind of loved that trait also along with the others about his little brother.

——

A/N

Not too sure about this. But still, hope you all like it.

“Yeah, Jack had me proper worried when he panicked for Joe” Caspar chuckled.

Joe’s eyes snapped open when he heard Jack’s name and panicked as he looked out for his friend.

“Jack… Jack…” Joe mumbled.

“Jack is alright. He’s right there” Zoe said as she pointed to Jack sleeping in the other bed.

“Calm down man. It’s all okay now” Caspar said, patting Joe’s shoulder.

“All okay” Joe repeated, slightly dozing off.

“All okay except the fact that you’re so stubborn. Look where you stubbornness led you.” Zoe shook her head.

“I’m sleeping” Joe whispered.

“Sure and when you wake we’ll talk about how you should listen to me next time” Zoe chuckled.

“I’m asleep” Joe told her.

They all had a good chuckle at that.

——

Being strong-willed did help Joe a lot. He used as a motivation to get his projects and collabs done. He used it at home to get his way around with his parents. It came to help when he was down in situations like these where his will power helps him power his way to recovery and help motivate his friend, Jack, recover as well. But it also costs him quite a few things. As Zoe says, that stubbornness would end him in big trouble sometime but like any other big sister, she kind of loved that trait also along with the others about his little brother.

——
